OL,6,FOpponents repeatedly called for Mr
OL,7,FMatheson to resign when the bill first
OL,8,Femerged in November last year,
OL,9,Fpointing to his claim to journalists
OL,10,Fthat there had been no personal use of
OL,11,Fthe device, before telling MSPs days
OL,12,Flater his sons had used the data.
OL,14,FAt the time, Mr Yousaf gave Mr
OL,15,FMatheson his backing.
OL,17,FMr Matheson added he had been
OL,18,F"enormously grateful" for the support
OL,19,FMr Yousaf gave to him and his family
OL,20,Fover the last year.
